The paper proposes a network formation game that explains the emergence of hierarchical structures in groups of self-interested individuals. This topic is related to game theory (cs.GT), social networks (cs.SOC), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and network science (cs.NE). The paper also considers the impact of well-motivated hierarchy promoting terms in the individuals' utility functions, which is related to social influence (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT, followed by cs.SOC, cs.MA, cs.NE, and cs.SI.
